 different machine learning algorithms?\\\",\\n                \\\"What is regularization?\\\",\\n                \\\"How do you evaluate the performance of a machine learning model?\\\",\\n            ],\\n            \\\"Cloud Computing\\\": [\\n                \\\"Explain the difference between IaaS, PaaS, and SaaS.\\\",\\n                \\\"What are the benefits of using cloud computing?\\\",\\n                \\\"How does cloud autoscaling work?\\\",\\n            ],\\n            \\\"AWS\\\": [\\n                \\\"What is EC2?\\\",\\n                \\\"What is S3?\\\",\\n                \\\"How do you deploy an application on AWS?\\\",\\n            ],\\n            \\\"Azure\\\": [\\n                \\\"What is Azure Virtual Machines?\\\",\\n                \\\"What is Azure Blob Storage?\\\",\\n                \\\"How do you deploy an application on Azure?\\\",\\n            ],\\n            \\\"Project Management\\\": [\\n                \\\"What are the different phases of project management?\\\",\\n                \\\"Explain Agile methodologies.\\\",\\n                \\\"How do you manage project risks?\\\",\\n            ]\\n        }\\n\\n    def generate_questions(self, num_questions=5):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Generates technical questions based on the job description and candidate resume.\\n        Args:\\n            num_questions (int): The number of questions to generate.\\n        Returns:\\n            list: A list of technical questions.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        relevant_skills = set(self.job_description['skills']).intersection(set(self.resume['skills']))\\n        questions = []\\n        for skill in relevant_skills:\\n            if skill in self.question_bank:\\n                questions.extend(self.question_bank[skill])\\n\\n        selected_questions = random.sample(questions, min(num_questions, len(questions))) # Avoid exceeding list length\\n        return selected_questions\\n\\n    def deliver_question(self, question):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Delivers a technical question to the candidate (simulated).\\n        Args:\\n            question (str): The technical question to deliver.\\n        Returns:\\n            None\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        print(f\\\"Question: {question}\\\")\\n\\n    def get_candidate_response(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Simulates getting a response from the candidate.\\n        Returns:\\n            str: The candidate's response.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        return input(\\\"Your Answer: \\\")\\n\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    # Example Usage\\n    job_description = {\\n        \\\"skills\\\": [\\\"Python\\\", \\\"Data Science\\\", \\\"Machine Learning\\\"],\\n        \\\"responsibilities\\\": [\\\"Develop machine learning models\\\", \\\"Analyze data\\\"]\\n    }\\n    resume = {\\n        \\\"skills\\\": [\\\"Python\\\", \\\"Data Science\\\", \\\"Machine Learning\\\", \\\"SQL\\\"],\\n        \\\"experience\\\": [\\\"Developed machine learning models using Python\\\"]\\n    }\\n\\n    interview_engine = InterviewEngine(job_description, resume)\\n    questions = interview_engine.generate_questions(num_questions=3)\\n\\n    for question in questions:\\n        interview_engine.deliver_question(question)\\n        candidate_response = interview_engine.get_candidate_response()\\n        print(f\\\"Candidate's Response: {candidate_response}\\\\n\\\")\\n```\\n\\n---\\n# **Downstream Tasks Objectives**\\nNo downstream objectives available.\\n\\n---\\n# **Current Task Requirements**\\nBuild the email service module in Python to send invitations, reminders, and notifications as needed\\n\\n---\\n\\n# **Required Output Format**\\nPython code\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gpt_response\": \"```python\\nimport smtplib\\nfrom email.mime.text import MIMEText\\n\\nclass EmailService:\\n    def __init__(self, smtp_server, port, sender_email, password):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Initializes the EmailService with SMTP server details and sender credentials.\\n        Args:\\n            smtp_server (str): The SMTP server address (e.g., 'smtp.gmail.com').\\n            port (int): The port number for the SMTP server (e.g., 587).\\n            sender_email (str): The sender's email address.\\n            password (str): The sender's email password or app password.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        self.smtp_server = smtp_server\\n        self.port = port\\n        self.sender_email = sender_email\\n        self.password = password\\n\\n    def send_email(self, recipient_email, subject, body):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Sends an email to the specified recipient.\\n        Args:\\n            recipient_email (str): The recipient's email address.\\n            subject (str): The subject of the email.\\n            body (str): The body of the email.\\n        Returns:\\n            bool: True if the email was sent successfully, False otherwise.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        msg = MIMEText(body)\\n        msg['Subject'] = subject\\n        msg['From'] = self.sender_email\\n        msg['To'] = recipient_email\\n\\n        try:\\n            server = smtplib.SMTP(self.smtp_server, self.port)\\n            server.starttls()  # Upgrade the connection to a secure TLS connection\\n            server.login(self.sender_email, self.password)\\n            server.sendmail(self.sender_email, recipient_email, msg.as_string())\\n            server.quit()\\n            return True\\n        except Exception as e:\\n            print(f\\\"Email sending failed: {e}\\\")\\n            return False\\n\\n    def send_interview_invitation(self, recipient_email, candidate_name, interview_time, job_title):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Sends an interview invitation email to the candidate.\\n        Args:\\n            recipient_email (str): The candidate's email address.\\n            candidate_name (str): The candidate's name.\\n            interview_time (str): The scheduled time for the interview.\\n            job_title (str): The title of the job the candidate is interviewing for.\\n        Returns:\\n            bool: True if the email was sent successfully, False otherwise.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        subject = f\\\"Interview Invitation for {job_title} at [Your Company]\\\"\\n        body = f\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Dear {candidate_name},\\n\\n        We are pleased to invite you to an interview for the {job_title} position at [Your Company].\\n\\n        The interview is scheduled for:\\n        Date and Time: {interview_time}\\n\\n        Please confirm your availability by replying to this email.\\n\\n        We look forward to meeting you.\\n\\n        Sincerely,\\n        [Your Name]\\n        [Your Company]\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        return self.send_email(recipient_email, subject, body)\\n\\n    def send_interview_reminder(self, recipient_email, candidate_name, interview_time, job_title):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Sends an interview reminder email to the candidate.\\n        Args:\\n            recipient_email (str): The candidate's email address.\\n            candidate_name (str): The candidate's name.\\n            interview_time (str): The scheduled time for the interview.\\n            job_title (str): The title of the job the candidate is interviewing for.\\n        Returns:\\n            bool: True if the email was sent successfully, False otherwise.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        subject = f\\\"Reminder: Interview for {job_title} at [Your Company]\\\"\\n        body = f\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Dear {candidate_name},\\n\\n        This is a friendly reminder about your upcoming interview for the {job_title} position at [Your Company].\\n\\n        The interview is scheduled for:\\n        Date and Time: {interview_time}\\n\\n        If you have any questions or need to reschedule, please contact us as soon as possible.\\n\\n        We look forward to meeting you.\\n\\n        Sincerely,\\n        [Your Name]\\n        [Your Company]\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        return self.send_email(recipient_email, subject, body)\\n\\n    def send_interview_notification(self, recipient_email, interviewer_name, candidate_name, interview_time, job_title):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Sends an interview notification email to the interviewer.\\n        Args:\\n            recipient_email (str): The interviewer's email address.\\n            interviewer_name (str): The interviewer's name.\\n            candidate_name (str): The candidate's name.\\n            interview_time (str): The scheduled time for the interview.\\n            job_title (str): The title of the job the candidate is interviewing for.\\n        Returns:\\n            bool: True if the email was sent successfully, False otherwise.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        subject = f\\\"Interview Notification: {candidate_name} for {job_title}\\\"\\n        body = f\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Dear {interviewer_name},\\n\\n        This is a notification that you have an interview scheduled with {candidate_name} for the {job_title} position.\\n\\n        The interview is scheduled for:\\n        Date and Time: {interview_time}\\n\\n        Please be prepared to conduct the interview.\\n\\n        Thank you,\\n        [Your Name]\\n        [Your Company]\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        return self.send_email(recipient_email, subject, body)\\n\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    # Example Usage (replace with your actual credentials)\\n    email_service = EmailService(\\n        smtp_server='smtp.gmail.com',\\n        port=587,\\n        sender_email='your_email@gmail.com',\\n        password='your_password'  # Use an app password if you have 2-factor authentication enabled\\n    )\\n\\n    # Example: Sending an interview invitation\\n    recipient_email = 'candidate@example.com'\\n    candidate_name = 'John Doe'\\n    interview_time = 'October 27, 2023, 10:00 AM'\\n    job_title = 'Software Engineer'\\n\\n    if email_service.send_interview_invitation(recipient_email, candidate_name, interview_time, job_title):\\n        print(\\\"Interview invitation sent successfully!\\\")\\n    else:\\n        print(\\\"Failed to send interview invitation.\\\")\\n\\n    # Example: Sending an interview reminder\\n    if email_service.send_interview_reminder(recipient_email, candidate_name, interview_time, job_title):\\n        print(\\\"Interview reminder sent successfully!\\\")\\n    else:\\n        print(\\\"Failed to send interview reminder.\\\")\\n\\n    # Example: Sending an interview notification to interviewer\\n    interviewer_email = 'interviewer@example.com'\\n    interviewer_name = 'Jane Smith'\\n    if email_service.send_interview_notification(interviewer_email, interviewer_name, candidate_name, interview_time, job_title):\\n        print(\\\"Interview notification sent successfully!\\\")\\n    else:\\n        print(\\\"Failed to send interview notification.\\\")\\n```\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-27T16:26:45.209243\"\n}"}
